&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supervise, schedule, and direct hourly, part-time, full-time, and temporary staff to ensure timely event execution and operational standards are met.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Train and mentor staff to maintain consistency, efficiency, and a high level of hospitality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage staffing levels to meet fluctuating event schedules while maintaining budget and labor efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Event Setup &amp;amp; Execution&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review event orders and floor plans to oversee the transformation of the venue for each event.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate and manage event setups, furniture placement, staging, and décor according to client specifications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the logistics and service between external catering partners, landlord/property management, and/or CHG culinary team and The Mallory’s onsite team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee vendor deliveries, load-ins, and load-outs, ensuring logistics run on schedule and comply with venue guidelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Foster a best-in-class hospitality experience while serving as the on-site point of contact for operations during events, resolving issues quickly and professionally.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure the venue and

&lt;p&gt;Convene Hospitality Group (CHG) operates a global portfolio of lifestyle brands focused on creating places and experiences that bring people together. The company designs, develops, and operates hospitality-driven destinations to host gatherings of all kinds, ranging from small corporate meetings to immersive brand activations and beyond. We love bringing people together in person, and that passion for great experiences extends to our employees as well. If you&#39;re interested in creating inspiring moments of connection, consider joining our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Event Services Supervisor | The Mallory, NYC&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hiring: NOW&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Location: Manhattan NYC (West Chelsea)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours: Full-time (40 hours)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Schedule: Seeking flexible availability due to varying event calendar. Monday through Friday, Nights, and Weekends as needed&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Compensation: $27/hour with eligibility for overtime any hours worked over 40 in a week (time and a half)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Mallory:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Mallory is Convene Hospitality Group’s premier new event destination located within the historic Terminal Warehouse in West Chelsea, New York. Reimagined from a landmark 19th-century freight hub into a dynamic 50,000-square-foot venue, The Mallory blends original industrial architecture with modern design and technology to host everything from galas and fashion shows to weddings and private celebrations for up to 550 guests. We are building a hospitality-oriented team dedicated to delivering thoughtful, high-touch experiences for every client and guest who step through our doors. Learn more about our space at: &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.themallorynyc.com&quot;&gt;https://www.themallorynyc.com.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a member of The Mallory&#39;s opening team, you&#39;ll play a key role in bringing one of New York City&#39;s most exciting new event venues to life. The Event Services Supervisor supports the day-to-day execution of events by partnering with our Event Producers, cross-functional teams, vendors, and catering partners to deliver seamless operations and exceptional guest experiences. This role is highly visible and hands-on, requiring an active presence on the venue floor throughout setup, execution, and breakdown while supervising our in-house hourly event staff and coordinating with catering partners. The ideal candidate is organized, solutions-oriented, and energized by being in a fast-paced, guest-facing environment with a wide range of event types and evolving operational needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to the Event Services Manager and the General Manager, the Event Services Supervisor supports the day-to-day execution of venue operations by coordinating event setups and supervising the on-shift event services team. This role helps ensure each space is prepared for successful events from setup through breakdown while delivering an exceptional guest experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Event Operations &amp;amp; Team Supervision&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supervise and direct in-house hourly event staff during setup, event execution, and breakdown.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate event setups, furniture placement, staging, deliveries, load-ins/outs, and venue readiness according to event orders and floor plans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with vendors, catering teams, property management, and internal departments to ensure seamless event execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as an on-site operational resource during events, resolving day-of issues and ensuring event spaces remain safe, organized, and guest-ready.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct pre- and post-event walkthroughs, monitor inventory, and report ma

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Barista, London&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Please note: candidate must currently reside in the UK and be able to work in the UK without sponsorship.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re seeking a Full Time Barista to join our Operations team at Convene&#39;s property located at 22 Bishopsgate. This role will report directly to the Conference &amp;amp; Events Manager.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Convene Hospitality Group (CHG) operates a global portfolio of lifestyle brands focused on creating places and experiences that bring people together. The company designs, develops, and operates hospitality-driven destinations to host gatherings of all kinds, ranging from small corporate meetings to immersive brand activations and beyond. We love bringing people together in person, and that passion for great experiences extends to our employees as well. If you&#39;re interested in creating inspiring moments of connection, consider joining our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;The Barista will provide genuine anticipatory service to clients and participants in all aspects of hospitality. In this position, you will interact with our clients and ensure they have a great experience at Convene. We need someone with excellent communication and interpersonal skills, as well as someone highly motivated and ready to work with others. Our employees carry our Core Values every day: Genuine, Relentless, Integrity, and Teamwork.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Greet all clients with enthusiasm and friendliness&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a warm and friendly demeanor at all times&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide world-class service, in accordance with our Brand Standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set up, replenish, maintain, and breakdown Food and Beverage stations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accommodate special client needs and last minute requests&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop relationships with clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accurately answer client questions about culinary and our spaces in a friendly manner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Read, understand, and execute Program Execution Orders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow checklists and Standard Operating Procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set up and breakdown conference rooms and refreshing rooms as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform facility maintenance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain safe, clean, organized, and well-stocked work areas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for constant sanitation, organization, and proper food handling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have full knowledge of menus, recipes, and other pertinent information&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform opening, mid-shift, and closing duties in accordance with company standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform cleaning duties including: wiping down tables and chairs, cleaning glasses, washing dishes, polishing glass and silverware, making rollups&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a professional appearance at all times&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain professional working relationships with the team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow all Company drink recipes and procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform additional duties as assigned&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Look For:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 1 year of Barista experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic knowledge of food and beverage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven excellent communication and interpersonal skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven good organizational skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be highly motivated and ready to lead other team members&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in multitasking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible and long hours are sometimes required&lt;/li&

&lt;p&gt;Yes Chef! At Convene we are all about bringing people together, to create unforgettable moments and events that leave our guests talking about us for not just weeks but in years to come. Our chefs are the true driving force that make our events stand out from the rest, creating incredible dishes that leave our clients and their guests wanting more every time.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Understanding that the Chef world is challenging, fun, and hard work we&amp;nbsp;usually&amp;nbsp;work on a&amp;nbsp;Monday-Friday&amp;nbsp;basis on a&amp;nbsp;40 hour contract&amp;nbsp;(it’s almost too good to be true right!? We even close for Christmas).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
