&lt;p&gt;Convene Hospitality Group is seeking a visionary leader to drive commercial success for NeueHouse, the ultimate private event venue and community for creators and innovators. NeueHouse Madison Square has been a creative catalyst setting the tone for NYC’s avant-garde membership club scene since 2011, with friends of the House including independent thinkers across fashion, music, publishing, entrepreneurship, and more. By powering NeueHouse with CHG&#39;s enterprise infrastructure, we are redefining the intersection of cultural membership, premium workspaces, and high-end experiential events.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About NeueHouse Madison Square&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Located in the heart of the Flatiron District, NeueHouse Madison Square is a landmark of New York’s creative scene, housed in a historic 1913 industrial building that once served as an auction house. NeueHouse Madison Square offers a timeless design, emotive experiences, and elevated hospitality.&amp;nbsp; Across eight floors, it offers special event spaces, membership lounges, private office suites, and a members-only restaurant and bar, all artfully blending an edgy, industrial aesthetic with the comfort and warmth of a designer residence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a dynamic, visionary executive to lead our NeueHouse MSQ Sales &amp;amp; Marketing efforts.&amp;nbsp; As NeueHouse’s Sales &amp;amp; Marketing Director, you will bridge the gap between lifestyle hospitality and enterprise sales. You will build the strategy that defines how we win, monetize, and amplify NeueHouse&#39;s unique offerings in our most mature market.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We want a leader who is passionate about how the meetings and events industry intersects with the nuances of private club membership and recognizes how technology is fundamentally transforming the way people work and gather.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will report directly to NeueHouse’s House Director and is a key leadership position for the company as we continue to invest in and elevate our original flagship location. The focus is on maximizing the use of space, strengthening member experience, and improving overall event flow within one of our most iconic houses. The location includes a penthouse with skyline views of the Chrysler Building, an 86-seat cinema for screenings and conversations, a flexible ground floor featuring a private restaurant and café, a fully reimagined second floor, and multiple boardrooms throughout the building.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver multi-million dollar revenue targets by deploying sales, marketing and pricing strategies based on market demand and seasonality.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Revenue Management, Centralized Sales and Brand Marketing to align regional campaigns, drive profitable demand across products and maximize client experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dynamically inform product design and service delivery based on client and member feedback&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sales presence should be engaging, approachable and build instant rapport

